    {
      "node_id": "chunk:history_of_australia_0",
      "passage_index": 12,
      "title": "History of Australia",
      "score": 0.04477824721384101,
      "text": "History of Australia\nThe Federal Capital Territory (FCT) was formed from New South Wales in 1911 to provide a location for the proposed new federal capital of Canberra (Melbourne was the seat of government from 1901 to 1927). The FCT was renamed the Australian Capital Territory (ACT) in 1938. The Northern Territory was transferred from the control of the South Australian government to the Commonwealth in 1911.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05223542552984765,
        "graph": 0.053495877241415996,
        "fact": 0.0
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:walnut_shade_missouri_0",
      "passage_index": 0,
      "title": "Walnut Shade, Missouri",
      "score": 0.044475697777889824,
      "text": "Walnut Shade, Missouri\nWalnut Shade is an unincorporated community in Taney County, Missouri, United States. It is located approximately six miles northwest of Forsyth on U.S. Route 160. The town sits at the confluence of Bull and Bear Creeks. Walnut Shade is part of the Branson, Missouri Micropolitan Statistical Area.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.052834070373966,
        "graph": 0.0513898635740284,
        "fact": 0.0
      }
    },
    {
      "node_id": "chunk:orroral_river_0",
      "passage_index": 13,
      "title": "Orroral River",
      "score": 0.0444428514489947,
      "text": "Orroral River\nOrroral River, a perennial stream of the Murrumbidgee catchment within the Murray-Darling basin, is located in the Australian Capital Territory, Australia.",
      "score_breakdown": {
        "dense": 0.05226456480083667,
