      "title": "Michael Lambert (snowboarder)",
      "score": 0.04216806865742494,
      "text": "Michael Lambert (snowboarder)\nMichael Lambert (born June 25, 1986) is a Canadian snowboarder who currently resides in Toronto, Ontario. Michael competes in the Alpine disciplines, Parallel GS and Parallel Slalom. Lambert has been on the Canadian National Team since 2002 and is currently working with coaches Mark Fawcett and Sylvain Jean. He is also the Slap cup champion of Stoney island",
      "score_breakdown": {
